, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1432–1468":"1432–1468","1409–1497":"1409–1497","1413–1497":"1413–1497","1434–1476":"1434–1476","1452–1487":"1452–1487","1480–Male":"1480–Deceased","–1505":"–1505","1390–Male":"1390–Deceased","1390–1433":"1390–1433","1451":"1451","1480":"1480","1390":"1390","1468":"1468","1413":"1413","1434":"1434","1433":"1433","1432":"1432","1487":"1487","1476":"1476","1497":"1497","1452":"1452","1409":"1409","1505":"1505","East Peckham, Kent, England":"East Peckham, Kent, England","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","Royden Haule Manor, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Royden","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Roydon (Essex), Roydon near Diss (Norfolk), Roydon near King’s Lynn (Norfolk), or Roydon Drift (Suffolk)."],"variants":[{"name":"Roydon","meanings":["English:  see  Royden  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sor Robert Royden 3rd Baron of Roydon Haule was born in 1432, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Roydon, was 42 and his mother, Lady Agnes Southwell Baroness Royden, was 42. He married Lady Cecily Inglethorpe Baroness Of Reydon in 1451. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in 1468, in his hometown, at the age of 36."},"et":{"1432–1468":"1432–1468","1409–1497":"1409–1497","1413–1497":"1413–1497","1434–1476":"1434–1476","1452–1487":"1452–1487","1480–Male":"1480–Surnud","–1505":"–1505","1390–Male":"1390–Surnud","1390–1433":"1390–1433","1451":"1451","1480":"1480","1390":"1390","1468":"1468","1413":"1413","1434":"1434","1433":"1433","1432":"1432","1487":"1487","1476":"1476","1497":"1497","1452":"1452","1409":"1409","1505":"1505","East Peckham, Kent, England":"East Peckham, Kent, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Royden Haule Manor, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1432–1468":"1432–1468","1409–1497":"1409–1497","1413–1497":"1413–1497","1434–1476":"1434–1476","1452–1487":"1452–1487","1480–Male":"1480–Kuollut","–1505":"–1505","1390–Male":"1390–Kuollut","1390–1433":"1390–1433","1451":"1451","1480":"1480","1390":"1390","1468":"1468","1413":"1413","1434":"1434","1433":"1433","1432":"1432","1487":"1487","1476":"1476","1497":"1497","1452":"1452","1409":"1409","1505":"1505","East Peckham, Kent, England":"East Peckham, Kent, England","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Royden Haule Manor, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1432–1468":"1432–1468","1409–1497":"1409–1497","1413–1497":"1413–1497","1434–1476":"1434–1476","1452–1487":"1452–1487","1480–Male":"1480–Décédé","–1505":"–1505","1390–Male":"1390–Décédé","1390–1433":"1390–1433","1451":"1451","1480":"1480","1390":"1390","1468":"1468","1413":"1413","1434":"1434","1433":"1433","1432":"1432","1487":"1487","1476":"1476","1497":"1497","1452":"1452","1409